1-19 17:19:59','2015-11-19 17:19:59','','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','news','','','2015-12-08 23:05:05','2015-12-08 23:05:05','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/?p=31',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(32,1,'2015-11-19 17:21:51','2015-11-19 17:21:51','THE BOARD OF PETWORTH HOUSE TENNIS COURT LTD (P.H.T.C.)\r\n\r\nTennis is played at Petworth House by courtesy of the National Trust and of the Rt. Hon. Lord Egremont. It is controlled by the Board of Directors, including a nominee of the National Trust, which is responsible for the upkeep of the structure of the court, and of Lord Egremont, who owns the estate.\r\n\r\nLord Egremont is the President of PHTC, and there are nine Vice-Presidents, all of whom have given distinguished service to PHTC over many years. These are N.W. Smith, D.J.E. Foster, B.L. Ellis, D.R. Brazier, Sir John Ritblat, M.E. Fairbarns, D.J.L. Godfray, J.C. Francis and S.W.Newton.\r\n\r\nPHTC has had six Chairmen since it was formed in 1960. The founder was Andy Dawson and he was the prime mover in the reopening of the court in 1960. In 1962 he became the first Chairman and served until 1974, when Eddie Harrison took over, serving until 1987. Then Captain Johnnie Coote became Chairman through to 1993, succeeded by Jack Phelps to 1994. David Godfray then became Chairman and held the office until he stood down in 2010. The Chairman is now Philip Robinson, and the Vice-Chairman is Robert Dolman.\r\n\r\nThe Board is made up of fourteen Directors including the Chairman and Vice-Chairman, and it controls club policy matters. Day to day management is in the hands of the Chairman, Andrew Falk (Hon, Secretary), Julian Wilkinson (Hon. Treasurer), Lucy Hutchinson (Hon. Membership Secretary), and Carolyn Armstrong-Smith (Hon. Fixtures Secretary). Other Directors are Simon Knight (the nominee of Lord Egremont and the National Trust), Charles Fuente, Carole Muir, Andrew Page, Nigel Draffan, Harvey Rawlings, David Fortune and Robert Muir.\r\n\r\nThe Board is supported by Chris Bray (Head Professional) and Tom Durack (Senior Professional). Other responsibilities are in the hands of David Fortune who is in charge of maintenance, and Nick Chambers who is Hon. Editor of the Newsletter.\r\n\r\nNovember 2015','The Board of Petworth House Tennis LTD (P.H.T.C)','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-11-19 17:21:51','2015-11-19 17:21:51','',11,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/19/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2015-11-19 17:21:59','2015-11-19 17:21:59','Tennis is played at Petworth House by courtesy of the National Trust and of the Rt. Hon. Lord Egremont. It is controlled by the Board of Directors, including a nominee of the National Trust, which is responsible for the upkeep of the structure of the court, and of Lord Egremont, who owns the estate.\r\n\r\nLord Egremont is the President of PHTC, and there are nine Vice-Presidents, all of whom have given distinguished service to PHTC over many years. These are N.W. Smith, D.J.E. Foster, B.L. Ellis, D.R. Brazier, Sir John Ritblat, M.E. Fairbarns, D.J.L. Godfray, J.C. Francis and S.W.Newton.\r\n\r\nPHTC has had six Chairmen since it was formed in 1960. The founder was Andy Dawson and he was the prime mover in the reopening of the court in 1960. In 1962 he became the first Chairman and served until 1974, when Eddie Harrison took over, serving until 1987. Then Captain Johnnie Coote became Chairman through to 1993, succeeded by Jack Phelps to 1994. David Godfray then became Chairman and held the office until he stood down in 2010. The Chairman is now Philip Robinson, and the Vice-Chairman is Robert Dolman.\r\n\r\nThe Board is made up of fourteen Directors including the Chairman and Vice-Chairman, and it controls club policy matters. Day to day management is in the hands of the Chairman, Andrew Falk (Hon, Secretary), Julian Wilkinson (Hon. Treasurer), Lucy Hutchinson (Hon. Membership Secretary), and Carolyn Armstrong-Smith (Hon. Fixtures Secretary). Other Directors are Simon Knight (the nominee of Lord Egremont and the National Trust), Charles Fuente, Carole Muir, Andrew Page, Nigel Draffan, Harvey Rawlings, David Fortune and Robert Muir.\r\n\r\nThe Board is supported by Chris Bray (Head Professional) and Tom Durack (Senior Professional). Other responsibilities are in the hands of David Fortune who is in charge of maintenance, and Nick Chambers who is Hon. Editor of the Newsletter.\r\n\r\nNovember 2015','The Board of Petworth House Tennis LTD (P.H.T.C)','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-11-19 17:21:59','2015-11-19 17:21:59','',11,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/19/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2015-11-19 17:25:31','2015-11-19 17:25:31','','200px-WyndhamArms','','inherit','open','closed','','200px-wyndhamarms','','','2015-11-19 17:25:31','2015-11-19 17:25:31','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/200px-WyndhamArms.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(37,1,'2015-11-20 11:49:57','2015-11-20 11:49:57','','images','','inherit','open','closed','','images','','','2015-11-20 11:49:57','2015-11-20 11:49:57','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/images.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(38,1,'2015-11-20 11:49:58','2015-11-20 11:49:58','','phtc_badge','','inherit','open','closed','','phtc_badge','','','2015-11-20 11:49:58','2015-11-20 11:49:58','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_badge.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(39,1,'2015-11-20 11:49:59','2015-11-20 11:49:59','','phtc_court_pano_best','','inherit','open','closed','','phtc_court_pano_best','','','2015-11-21 10:57:25','2015-11-21 10:57:25','',79,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_court_pano_best.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(40,1,'2015-11-20 11:50:00','2015-11-20 11:50:00','','phtc_court_pano','','inherit','open','closed','','phtc_court_pano','','','2015-11-20 13:47:37','2015-11-20 13:47:37','',47,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_court_pano.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(41,1,'2015-11-20 11:50:01','2015-11-20 11:50:01','','phtc_racquet','','inherit','open','closed','','phtc_racquet','','','2015-11-20 11:50:01','2015-11-20 11:50:01','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_racquet.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(42,1,'2015-11-20 11:50:35','2015-11-20 11:50:35','http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/cropped-phtc_court_pano_best.jpg','cropped-phtc_court_pano_best.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-phtc_court_pano_best-jpg','','','2015-11-20 13:40:14','2015-11-20 13:40:14','',47,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/cropped-phtc_court_pano_best.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(43,1,'2015-11-20 11:55:22','2015-11-20 11:55:22','','phtc_court_pano_best_360x80','','inherit','open','closed','','phtc_court_pano_best_360x80','','','2015-11-20 11:55:22','2015-11-20 11:55:22','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_court_pano_best_360x80.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(44,3,'2015-11-20 13:31:45','2015-11-20 13:31:45','It was another busy weekend for Petworth both at the club and for some players in the British Open.\r\n\r\n<strong>Petworth v Old Harrovians – Sunday 15th Nov</strong>\r\nPetworth hosted the Old Harrovians and the match was very close going down to the last match of the day. Petworth won the match 3/2 with some very good tennis played throughout the day and I am told that the curry for lunch was up to match manager David Fortune’s usual high standard!\r\n\r\n<strong>Night Pennant – Sunday 15th November</strong>\r\nOne Direction drew 3 sets all with the Moral Hazards but won the match with more games won so they get the win 5 points to 4\r\n\r\n<strong>British Open – Played at Queens Club</strong>\r\nPetworth had three players taking part in the main draw of 24 players. Charlie Braham put up a great fight to push Manchester Professional Darren Long (h’cap 1) to 5 sets but sadly could not quite get the win. Adam Dolman’s opponent was Queens Head Pro Andrew Lyons who had to retire at 4/4 in the first set so Adam went through to play World no 4 Bryn Sayers in the second round. Sadly Adam did not win this one. I won my first round match against Marc Seigneur but came up against World no 3 Steve Virgona yesterday and lost in straight sets. Louis Gordon is partnering Adam Player in the doubles and they played a great match to win in the first round and they now play no 2 seeds Ben Matthews and Kieran Booth tomorrow afternoon. Good luck\r\n\r\nA big congratulations to both Charlie and Adam on reaching their first British Open main draw and great experience for them both!\r\n\r\n<strong>Courts this week and weekend</strong>\r\nFriday 20th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45 and 20.15\r\n\r\nSaturday 21st November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 16.30, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n\r\nSunday 22nd November\r\nCourts available to book at 09.00, 19.00 and 20.15 – Louis available for a lesson at 09.00\r\n\r\nIf any of these courts suit you then do book online at <a href=\"http://www.realtennisonline.com/bookings\">www.realtennisonline.com/bookings</a> or call myself or Louis at the club on 01798 343527.','Week of 16th November - News/results at PHTC','','publish','open','open','','week-of-16th-november-newsresults-at-phtc','','','2015-12-09 10:10:32','2015-12-09 10:10:32','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/?p=44',0,'post','',0),(45,1,'2015-11-20 13:27:38','2015-11-20 13:27:38','It was another busy weekend for Petworth both at the club and for some players in the British Open.\r\n \r\nPetworth v Old Harrovians – Sunday 15th Nov\r\nPetworth hosted the Old Harrovians and the match was very close going down to the last match of the day.  Petworth won the match 3/2 with some very good tennis played throughout the day and I am told that the curry for lunch was up to match manager David Fortune’s usual high standard!\r\n \r\nNight Pennant – Sunday 15th November\r\nOne Direction drew 3 sets all with the Moral Hazards but won the match with more games won so they get the win 5 points to 4\r\n \r\nBritish Open – Played at Queens Club\r\nPetworth had three players taking part in the main draw of 24 players.  Charlie Braham put up a great fight to push Manchester Professional Darren Long (h’cap 1) to 5 sets but sadly could not quite get the win.  Adam Dolman’s opponent was Queens Head Pro Andrew Lyons who had to retire at 4/4 in the first set so Adam went through to play World no 4 Bryn Sayers in the second round.  Sadly Adam did not win this one.  I won my first round match against Marc Seigneur but came up against World no 3 Steve Virgona yesterday and lost in straight sets.  Louis Gordon is partnering Adam Player in the doubles and they played a great match to win in the first round and they now play no 2 seeds Ben Matthews and Kieran Booth tomorrow afternoon. Good luck\r\n \r\nA big congratulations to  both Charlie and Adam on reaching their first British Open main draw and great experience for them both!\r\n \r\nCourts this week and weekend\r\nFriday 20th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45 and 20.15\r\n \r\nSaturday 21st November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 16.30, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n \r\nSunday 22nd November\r\nCourts available to book at 09.00, 19.00 and 20.15 – Louis available for a lesson at 09.00\r\n \r\nIf any of these courts suit you then do book online at www.realtennisonline.com/bookings or call myself or Louis at the club on 01798 343527.','Week of 16th November - News/results at PHTC','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2015-11-20 13:27:38','2015-11-20 13:27:38','',44,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/20/44-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(46,1,'2015-11-20 13:33:00','2015-11-20 13:33:00','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!','Hello world!','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-revision-v1','','','2015-11-20 13:33:00','2015-11-20 13:33:00','',1,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/20/1-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(47,1,'2015-11-20 13:34:52','2015-11-20 13:34:52','&nbsp;\r\n<a href=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_court_pano.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-40\" src=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/phtc_court_pano.jpg\" alt=\"phtc_court_pano\" width=\"1198\" height=\"263\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Petworth House Tennis Court (P.H.T.C.) website has been created principally for the benefit of the club members; but non-members are most welcome to browse the site for their own interest. It is hoped that all visitors to the site will enjoy the sections on the history of the court and of Tennis at Petworth House, and of the Professionals who have worked there since 1900.\r\n\r\nWe have a junior section for which the annual subscription is much reduced, and we encourage the development of new talent with free or subsidised coaching by our high ranking Professionals.\r\n\r\nAdults who have not played Tennis previously are invited to have one or two lessons to become acquainted with the game before applying to join. The summer is the best time to do this when the court is more available.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to visit the court to watch Real Tennis being played, or if you would like to enquire about membership and subscription rates, please contact the Professionals who will be pleased to supply you with further information. Contact details can be found on the <a href=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/contact-us/\">“Contact Us”</a> page.','Welcome to our Website','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2015-11-20 13:49:15','2015-11-20 13:49:15','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/?page_id=47',0,'page','',0),(48,1,'2015-11-20 13:34:52','2015-11-20 13:34:52','Welcome to the Website o