etersen.co.uk/?p=194',0,'post','',0),(195,1,'2015-11-21 14:41:04','2015-11-21 14:41:04','Just a short line to congratulate two of PHTC members Adam Dolman and Charlie Braham on winning their British Open Qualifying matches yesterday at Radley College.\r\n \r\nThey now progress through to join me in the main draw which starts tomorrow at the Queens Club.\r\n \r\nOrder of play is below:\r\nSunday 15th November \r\n\r\n10am – Darren Long v Charlie Braham\r\n\r\n12 noon – A Lyons v Adam Dolman\r\n\r\n2pm – Conor Medlow v Ed Kay\r\n\r\n4pm – Robert Shenkman v Craig Greenhalgh\r\n\r\n6pm Tom Durack v Mark Seigneur\r\n\r\nIf you would like to buy tickets for any of the British Open then please follow this link: <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/o/tournament-administration-tampra-8167609838\">http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/o/tournament-administration-tampra-8167609838</a>\r\n\r\nThe British Open runs from tomorrow through until Tuesday 24th November.','PHTC Success in British Open Qualifying','','inherit','closed','closed','','194-revision-v1','','','2015-11-21 14:41:04','2015-11-21 14:41:04','',194,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/21/194-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(196,3,'2015-11-10 14:42:24','2015-11-10 14:42:24','It was another busy weekend at the club with two National League matches, a Sunday match and a Night Pennant!\r\n \r\nNational League - Saturday\r\nRichard White lead his division 8 team to a comfortable 2/1 win against Holyport which leaves them in a healthy third place in the table.  In division 7 we had a very strong team but sadly just lost out to an even stronger Leamington team 3/0 but well played to all players involved  - the hard work will pay off!\r\n \r\nPetworth v Newmarket - Sunday\r\nPetworth hosted Newmarket on Sunday and with some great play from all players the match ended in a 2/2 draw which I think all players were please with and as usual everyone was treated to a great lunch!\r\n \r\nNight Pennant – Sunday\r\nThe Ladies & The Tramp proved too strong for The Moral Hazards taking the win 6 points to 2\r\n \r\nCourts this week and weekend\r\nThursday 12th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45\r\n \r\nFriday 13th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n \r\nSaturday 14th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 12.45, 14.00, 16.30, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n \r\nIf any of these courts suit you then do book online at <a href=\"http://www.realtennisonline.com/bookings\">www.realtennisonline.com/bookings</a> or call myself or Louis at the club on 01798 343527.','News/results at PHTC and courts available this week/weekend','','publish','open','open','','newsresults-at-phtc-and-courts-available-this-weekweekend','','','2015-11-21 14:48:03','2015-11-21 14:48:03','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/?p=196',0,'post','',0),(197,1,'2015-11-21 14:44:00','2015-11-21 14:44:00','It was another busy weekend at the club with two National League matches, a Sunday match and a Night Pennant!\r\n \r\nNational League - Saturday\r\nRichard White lead his division 8 team to a comfortable 2/1 win against Holyport which leaves them in a healthy third place in the table.  In division 7 we had a very strong team but sadly just lost out to an even stronger Leamington team 3/0 but well played to all players involved  - the hard work will pay off!\r\n \r\nPetworth v Newmarket - Sunday\r\nPetworth hosted Newmarket on Sunday and with some great play from all players the match ended in a 2/2 draw which I think all players were please with and as usual everyone was treated to a great lunch!\r\n \r\nNight Pennant – Sunday\r\nThe Ladies & The Tramp proved too strong for The Moral Hazards taking the win 6 points to 2\r\n \r\nCourts this week and weekend\r\nThursday 12th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45\r\n \r\nFriday 13th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n \r\nSaturday 14th November\r\nCourt available to book at 07.45, 12.45, 14.00, 16.30, 19.00 and 20.15\r\n \r\nIf any of these courts suit you then do book online at <a href=\"http://www.realtennisonline.com/bookings\">www.realtennisonline.com/bookings</a> or call myself or Louis at the club on 01798 343527.','News/results at PHTC and courts available this week/weekend','','inherit','closed','closed','','196-revision-v1','','','2015-11-21 14:44:00','2015-11-21 14:44:00','',196,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/21/196-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(198,3,'2015-11-03 14:45:07','2015-11-03 14:45:07','Last weekend we had some fantastic tennis played at the club with both singles and doubles being played.\r\n\r\n<strong>Andy Dawson A Grade Singles Final - 2014</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/andy_dawson_finalists.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-201 alignright\" src=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/andy_dawson_finalists.jpg\" alt=\"andy_dawson_finalists\" width=\"444\" height=\"333\" data-id=\"201\" /></a>On Saturday we had one of the largest crowds I have seen for a final and it was a good job too as this one of the best quality finals of the year between Luke Danby and Adam Dolman. Adam stormed out of the gates and into a 4/1 lead, but Luke managed to step up his game and got the set back to 5/5, he then played a very solid game to close out the set 6 games to 5. In the second set it was Luke who took the lead with such strong forcing that he even had those watching in the dedans flinching! Although Adam started to creep back into the match, he could not quite get back on level terms and Luke closed out the match for his 6th Andy Dawson title.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ellis Rich Scratch Doubles - 2015</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ellis_rich_winners.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-206 alignleft\" src=\"http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ellis_rich_winners.jpg\" alt=\"ellis_rich_winners\" width=\"372\" height=\"279\" data-id=\"206\" /></a>The Final had three of the players from last year’s final playing once again but this year a different outcome. The new pairing of Luke Danby and Mark Drysdale took on the defending champs Adam Dolman and Andrew Page. Luke and Mark started very strongly going into a 4/1 lead but Adam and Andrew managed to win 2 very quick games from the hazard end and get right back into contention. The first set was edged 6/4 by Mark and Luke. In the second set Luke and Mark looked very strong with Luke dominating the court from the service end and they closed the match out 6/4 6/3. Thank you to Brian Rich and Brian Ellis for presenting the trophies and for supporting this great tournament which is now in its 33rd year.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ellis Rich Results</strong>\r\nQuarter Finals\r\nL Danby/M Drysdale bt J Petersen/C O’Donnell W/O\r\nG Russell/ R Williams bt N Chambers/S Calder-Smith 6/2 6/5\r\nN Harris/H Rawlings bt M Marcar/B Chambers 5/6 6/3 6/1\r\nA Page/A Dolman bt A Falk/S Armstrong 6/2 6/0\r\n\r\nSemi Finals\r\nA Page/A Dolman bt H Rawlings/N Harris 3/6 6/2 6/0\r\nM Drysdale/ L Danby bt G Russell/ R Williams 6/2 6/1\r\n\r\nFinal\r\nM Drysdale/ L Danby bt A Page/A Dolman 6/4 6/3\r\n\r\nCongratulations to our winners and to all of those that competed in w great weekend of tennis.','Ellis Rich and Andy Dawson Report and results','','publish','open','open','','ellis-rich-and-andy-dawson-report-and-results','','','2015-11-21 15:26:01','2015-11-21 15:26:01','',0,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/?p=198',0,'post','',0),(199,1,'2015-11-21 14:46:19','2015-11-21 14:46:19','Last weekend we had some fantastic tennis played at the club with both singles and doubles being played.\r\n \r\nAndy Dawson A Grade Singles Final - 2014\r\nOn Saturday we had one of the largest crowds I have seen for a final and it was a good job too as this one of the best quality finals of the year between Luke Danby and Adam Dolman.  Adam stormed out of the gates and into a 4/1 lead, but Luke managed to step up his game and got the set back to 5/5, he then played a very solid game to close out the set 6 games to 5.  In the second set it was Luke who took the lead with such strong forcing that he even had those watching in the dedans flinching!  Although Adam started to creep back into the match, he could not quite get back on level terms and Luke closed out the match for his 6th Andy Dawson title.\r\n \r\nEllis Rich Scratch Doubles - 2015\r\nThe Final had three of the players from last year’s final playing once again but this year a different outcome.  The new pairing of Luke Danby and Mark Drysdale took on the defending champs Adam Dolman and Andrew Page.  Luke and Mark started very strongly going into a 4/1 lead but Adam and Andrew managed to win 2 very quick games from the hazard end and get right back into contention.  The first set was edged 6/4 by Mark and Luke.  In the second set Luke and Mark looked very strong with Luke dominating the court from the service end and they closed the match out 6/4 6/3.  Thank you to Brian Rich and Brian Ellis for presenting the trophies and for supporting this great tournament which is now in its 33rd year.\r\n \r\nEllis Rich Results\r\nQuarter Finals\r\nL Danby/M Drysdale bt J Petersen/C O’Donnell W/O\r\nG Russell/ R Williams bt N Chambers/S Calder-Smith  6/2 6/5\r\nN Harris/H Rawlings bt M Marcar/B Chambers 5/6 6/3 6/1\r\nA Page/A Dolman bt A Falk/S Armstrong 6/2 6/0\r\n \r\nSemi Finals\r\nA Page/A Dolman bt H Rawlings/N Harris 3/6 6/2 6/0\r\nM Drysdale/ L Danby bt G Russell/ R Williams 6/2 6/1\r\n \r\nFinal\r\nM Drysdale/ L Danby bt A Page/A Dolman 6/4 6/3\r\n \r\nCongratulations to our winners and to all of those that competed in w great weekend of tennis.','Ellis Rich and Andy Dawson Report and results','','inherit','closed','closed','','198-revision-v1','','','2015-11-21 14:46:19','2015-11-21 14:46:19','',198,'http://phtcdev.jonpetersen.co.uk/2015/11/21/198-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(200,1